	</mediaobject>
</screenshot>
</para>
<para>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Execution speed</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Sets the duration of one simulation cycle. Possible range is from 1ms to 1s. 
The minimal useful value depends upon your system.
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Fast as possible</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Enable this check box if you want the fastest simulation. &kapp; starts a new 
simulation cycle immediately after completing the last one.
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Simulation time per tick</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Set the simulation time per simulation cycle. This means the amount of time 
that you would like to emulate for each simulation cycle. Possible range is 
from 100ps to 1s. 
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Synchronized to execution speed</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Enable this check box if you want to synchronize the simulation time to the execution speed.
This means not mandantory real time, because this depends on the system load and the exection
time of a simulation cycle.
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>View update speed</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Set the update time of the GUI here. Possible range is from 1ms to 1s. The 
update is always synchronised to the execution speed. This means that the 
update speed can not be faster than the execution speed. 
<tip><para>Lower the update speed if the system load is too high.</para></tip>
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Synchronized to execution speed</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Enable this check box if you want to synchronize the update speed to the execution speed.
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

</variablelist>
</para>

</listitem> </varlistentry>

