</para>
<para>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Package directories</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Lets you select directories which contain &kapp; package files. All package 
files in this and all subdirectories will be loaded at application startup. 
The default is <filename>$KDEDIR/lib/ksimus/</filename>.
</para>
<para>
<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Browse</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Opens a file dialog and lets you select an additional directory. After the selection the
directory is shown in the single line edit field. You can modify it and/or add it with
the Add button to the list.
<remark>The directory is not added before you press the Add button!</remark>
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Add</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Adds a directory from the single line edit field to the package directory list. 
If the single edit line is empty or the directory exists already in the list, nothing is done.
<remark>The package file configuration is only evaluated at application startup. 
Because of this, the new configuration for &kapp; is not recognised until the 
application is restarted.
</remark>
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Remove</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Removes the highlighted directory from the package directory list.
<remark>The package file configuration is only evaluated at application startup. 
Because of this, the new configuration for &kapp; is not recognised until the 
application is restarted.
</remark>
</para></listitem></varlistentry>


</variablelist>
</para></listitem></varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term><guilabel>Package files</guilabel>
</term><listitem><para>
Lets you select single &kapp; package files. This is useful if you develop your own package
file, because you don't need to install it for testing. The default is no files.
</para>
<para>
The usage of <guilabel>Package files</guilabel> is similar to the use of
<guilabel>Package directories</guilabel>.
</para></listitem></varlistentry>




</variablelist>
</para>
