<sect1 id="working-view">
<title>The Working View</title>
<para>
This chapter describes the different kind of the Working Views.
</para>


<!-- ############################################################################### -->
<!-- ########################         Schematic View        ######################## -->
<!-- ############################################################################### -->
<sect2 id="working-view-schematic">
<title>The Schematic View</title>
<para>
Develop your network or circuit at the Schematic View.
</para><para>
Features:
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>
Select the &components; from the &componentSupplier; and place them onto the view.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
&Wire; the connectors or &wires; with drag and drop.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Use the context sensitive popup menus. There are four different areas:
	<itemizedlist>
	<listitem><para>
	&Components;
	</para></listitem>
	<listitem><para>
	&Connectors;
	</para></listitem>
	<listitem><para>
	&Wires;
	</para></listitem>
	<listitem><para>
	Empty Area
	</para></listitem>
	</itemizedlist>
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Select a single &component; with a right mouse click. Collect multiple 
components with a right mouse click on each component while pressing the
<keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap></keycombo> key.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Select multiple components with rectangle select mode. Press the right mouse
button on an empty area, enlarge the rectangle until all components are covered and
then release the mouse button.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Copy and past components. &Wires; between copied components are copied also.
Wires between a copied component and a not copied component are not copied.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Move components with drag and drop. Don't worry about the wires.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Use the multiple undo and redo mechanism.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
See the status bar while the mouse pointer moves over &components; or &connectors;.
</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
Resize the Schematic View with the handles on each corner.
</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
</para>


</sect2>

<!-- ############################################################################### -->
<!-- ########################     User Interface View       ######################## -->
<!-- ############################################################################### -->
<sect2 id="working-view-user">
<title>The User Interface View</title>
<para>
Design the User Interface for your network or circuit at this view. The view shows all
GUI components (e.g. Buttons, LEDs) from the &schematicView;.
</para>
